    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a79fdf83_4759b508",
        "filename": "appengine/mapper/job.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 30,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-25T18:51:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is there really a need elsewhere for this? Mapper if the only library that needs it so far. And it doesn\u0027t need generic query structures (there\u0027s a lot of stuff that makes no sense to put in mapper\u0027s queries: order, limits, cursors, etc).\n\nIf we move this into luci/gae, we\u0027ll have to make it general enough to be able to serialize all queries. But this is not needed in the mapper (the only client so far), and in fact harmful (we\u0027ll have to add checks that forbid unneeded stuff).\n\nThus I believe moving this to luci/gae is a waste of time.",
      "parentUuid": "abf46f76_b521c9ca",
